dcterms:description: The PTB Diagnostics dataset contains ECG records from 290 people, with various diagnoses including myocardial infarction and healthy samples. It is used for classifying ECG signals.
dcterms:title: PTB Diagnostics dataset

dcterms:description: Natural Visibility Graph (NVG) is a method for transforming time series data into graphs based on visibility principles, where nodes represent data points and edges represent visibility connections.
dcterms:title: Natural Visibility Graph (NVG)

dcterms:creator: B. Luque
L. Lacasa
F. Ballesteros
J. Luque
dcterms:description: Horizontal Visibility Graph (HVG) is a simplified method for transforming time series into graphs, connecting nodes based on horizontal visibility criteria.
dcterms:title: Horizontal Visibility Graph (HVG)

dcterms:creator: A.S. Campanharo
M.I. Sirer
R.D. Malmgren
F.M. Ramos
L.A.N. Amaral
dcterms:description: Quantile Graph (QG) is a method that transforms time series data into graphs by dividing the data into quantiles, where each quantile represents a node in the graph.
dcterms:title: Quantile Graph (QG)

dcterms:creator: M. Kachuee

dcterms:description: The PTB Diagnostic ECG (preprocessed) dataset is a version of the PTB Diagnostics dataset that has undergone preprocessing for ECG heartbeat classification.
dcterms:title: PTB Diagnostic ECG (preprocessed)
